<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6a7b1e7-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s31302"><num value="31302">§ 31302.</num><heading> Availability of instruments, copies, and information</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary shall—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6a7b1e8-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s31302/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> make any instrument filed or recorded with the Secretary under this chapter available for public inspection;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6a7b1e9-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s31302/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> on request, provide a copy, including a certified copy, of any instrument made available for public inspection under this chapter; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6a7b1ea-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s31302/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> on request, provide a certificate containing information included in an instrument filed or recorded under this chapter.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idf6a7b1eb-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/100/710/tI/s102/c">Pub. L. 100–710, title I, § 102(c)</ref>, <date date="1988-11-23">Nov. 23, 1988</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/102/4740">102 Stat. 4740</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/111/281/tIX/s913/a/1">Pub. L. 111–281, title IX, § 913(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="2010-10-15">Oct. 15, 2010</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/3017">124 Stat. 3017</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
